<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hereditary" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hereditary,</orth> possessed by inheritance, transmitted from parent to child: <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.223" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 223</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 4, 13</bibl>. Somewhat improperly: <cit><quote>these old fellows have their ingratitude in them h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.224" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 224</bibl></cit> (== inherent, natural).
